type: SURVEY
files: dspy/streaming/streaming_listener.py
note: Confirmed: my _last_chunk_ts refresh is NOT inside the 'if self.stream_start:' block. It goes right after the existing try/except that extracts chunk_message, i.e. immediately after:
        try:
            chunk_message = chunk.choices[0].delta.content
            if chunk_message is None:
                return
        except Exception:
            return
I add a new line there (something like: self._last_chunk_ts = now_ts_helper() or similar), before the 'if chunk_message and start_identifier in chunk_message:' line. That's a standalone line not touching your start-detection/rolling-end/emit-chunk log sites. And yes, 'end of receive' in my earlier message just meant appending the new tick() method as a new function after receive() (and before flush()) - not editing receive()'s return statement. So true overlaps are only: __init__ (sig+body) and the top-of-receive 'if self.stream_end: if self.allow_reuse:' reset block. Ready to co-draft those two now.

